            "id": "recFn1H7WWroacWx8",
            "term": 1,
            "sort": "",
            "content": "[ ] (Plutarch: Beginner Track) [This article and video](https://greekreporter.com/2024/06/09/plutarch-biographer-alexander-the-great-greeks/) give some background on Plutarch, the biographer of Publicola. \n[ ] (Plutarch: Beginner Track) Explore [this timeline](https://www.heritage-history.com/index.php?c=resources&s=study-cat&h=ancient_rome&f=timeline) of Ancient Rome.\n[ ] (Current Events) Explore how to spot 16 types of media bias you can spot throughout the year.\n[ ] (Current Events) Parent/Teacher Resource for help in discussing news topics with children—Concurrently: The News Coach Podcast"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "term": 2,
        "title": "Term 2",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "recElrnv7gf7HDK0O",
            "term": 2,
            "sort": "",
            "content": "[ ] (Plutarch: Beginner Track) View [maps](https://www.heritage-history.com/index.php?c=resources&s=study-page&h=ancient_rome&f=historical_maps) of some Roman cities.\n[ ] (Plutarch: Beginner Track) Watch [this video](https://youtu.be/_Wl6IJl2AHM?si=7ptzitfx2qNqzUJi) about the Temple of Jupiter."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "term": 3,
        "title": "Term 3",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "recEbhwj7GBUiPssd",
            "term": 3,
            "sort": "",
            "content": "[ ] (Plutarch: Beginner Track) If Plutarch were alive today, what political or military leaders do you think he would write about? Write a modern version of Plutarch's Lives featuring one (or comparing two) of these modern leaders. \n[ ] (Plutarch: Beginner Track) Explore the Plutarch Podcast and other resources available on [this website](https://grammaticus.co/resources-for-reading-plutarch/). (Teachers should preview all content.)"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
